<LEADPARA>  For the first time since scores of Hindus were killed last winter when they
battled security forces in this holy Hindu town, hundreds of thousands of
pilgrims traveled peacefully to a shrine here in the last week.;    According
to one district official, more than 1 million Hindus, largely poor, barefoot
and enthusiastic, visited the site March 24, the birthday of the Hindu god
Rama.  </LEADPARA>
